Prosoma.
Carapace reddish-brown, densely covered with white setae, with anterior heart-shaped yellow median band just behind PLEs and fovea (
Fig. 33
); marginal stripes absent (
Fig. 33
). Sternum yellow, covered with short white and sparse long black setae (
Fig. 34
). Chelicerae almost yellow, with reddish-brown distal ends, covered with dense white and sparse black setae (
Fig. 35
). Clypeus yellow, covered with dense white and sparse black setae (
Fig. 35
). Endites brown anteriorly and yellow posteriorly, labium brown, covered with black setae (
Fig. 34
).
